TimeStamp: What is a Timestamp.


Number of Seconds from 1st january 1970 GMT Time.---->
It keeps on increasing . 

UnixTimestamp is always same. it doenst change as per country . but time changes as per country.

any time value that is a unix time stamp is same and a standard measure of time. 

9:45 PM IST, GMT, Australia Time.


Javascript: Usually it takes timestamp value in milliseconds. 

javascript time stamp = 1000 * normal timestamp;


let dateOb = new Date(timestamp in milliseconds);


Strings:
In Javascript you can create strings with 2 ways. 
1) standard way which we have been doing so far. ex let name = "sumit";
2) using String Constructor. let name = new String("sumit");